p: W.H. Pinkney being first duly sworn on oath says that he has the within named Ah Ken in his custody by virtue of a judgement of conviction & fine rendered by Justice G.A. Hill Seattle Precinct rendered & commitment issued in of said judgement
Subscribed & sworn to before me this 23 day of Feb 1887
appn for writ of Habeas Corpus of Ah Kan (Chinaman)
Return to writ of Habeas Corpus by W.H. Pinkney
By James P Ludlerr Deputy Clerk
